		.row.bg
			a#about
			.large-6.medium-12.small-12.columns
				h2 About Us
				p We are Hotel California, a group of burners from the Bay Area.  Our camp is a community of 60 new and returning members coming from all over the world, and our infrastructure includes a full kitchen, a communal dome, a workshop dome, a large shade structure covering tents, a shower, first aid supplies, a kickass sound system, a climbing wall, a custom bar, and a very, very large fire pit. We have a large-ish storage space on Treasure Island, and two 20’ shipping containers to transport our camp elements, our art piece and firewood. Come say hi to us in 2016 at 7:15 and Guild.

				p We provide a safe, responsible and interactive playground to all of our members. We expect of all of our members #[strong radical involvement] – in other words contribute to all camp chores and activities (camp set up and tear down, kitchen duties, bar duties, ice runs) and keep the camp free of MOOP. Don’t worry, you will have plenty of time to explore the Playa, party, make friends, attend workshops, go on adventures, or anything your little heart desires. We also ask that you stay the whole duration of the burn – arrive on Monday at the latest, and stay as long as you can, preferably until the man burns. We are not a turn-key camp, or plug-and-play camp, and we’re not your Mom.

				p If you would like to join us this year, #[a(href="https://www.facebook.com/groups/144960355700052/") apply here]. Spots are limited and we are fully booked every year before departure!

